data.name: How to Enter GTA 5
data.part1: How to Enter GTA 5 (Grand Theft Auto V) Cheat Codes on PlayStation, Xbox and PC
data.part2: As you would expect, the procedure of entering cheat codes is different on different platforms. This includes Grand Theft Auto V for PlayStation, Xbox and PC. One common way for all platforms is to press ‘up’ to bring up the cell phone, and enter codes to activate special powers and helicopters. Apart from that, each platform has its own set of commands, which you can execute to enable specific features in the game. On PC, gamers can also use the ‘~’ key to bring up the command enter box, and type the cheat code to activate powers in the game. The key combinations for each platform and the respective codes are mentioned alongside the cheats below.

data.name: God Mode in GTA 5
data.part1:
What is God Mode in GTA 5 and How to Use It? 
 God Mode in GTA 5 is a special mode that allows the player’s character to be invincible and immune to any attack. However, the only downside of the model is that it is activated for only five minutes. So, if a player wants to activate the God Mode for a longer period of time, they have to enter the cheat code again and again after five minutes intervals. You can enter God Mode in GTA 5 by using your cellphone in the game or by simply entering the cheat codes. Here’s a list of cheat codes for God Mode on different platforms:
data.part2:
PC: PAINKILLER 
 PS3/PS4: RIGHT, X, RIGHT, LEFT, RIGHT, R1, RIGHT, LEFT, X, TRIANGLE 
 Xbox 360/Xbox One: Right, A, RIGHT, LEFT, RIGHT, RB, RIGHT, LEFT, A, Y 
 Cell Phone: 1-999-724-654-5537 (1-999-PAINKILLER)

data.name: Tesla in GTA 5
data.part1: Is there a Tesla in GTA 5?
data.part2: Yes, a version of Tesla Roadster is there in the GTA 5 game. The car is known as Voltic, which was developed by a fictional company known as Coil. One can buy the Voltic aka Tesla Roadster, in the game via the Legendary Motorsports website for $150,000.
